    <item>
      <title>Re: [bug] wrong RewriteRule in ezcore/doc/ajax.txt</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezcore/forum/general/bug_wrong_rewriterule_in_ezcore_doc_ajax_txt/re_bug_wrong_rewriterule_in_ezcore_doc_ajax_txt</link>
      <description>I'm not so sure that rewrite rule will work in all setups, the rewrite rule is taken from the existing ezp rules.&#13;
&#13;
doc:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
        RewriteRule content/treemenu/? /index_treemenu.php [L]&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
.htaccess_root:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
RewriteRule content/treemenu/? index_treemenu.php&#13;
RewriteRule index_treemenu.php - [L]&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
So I just guess there is a reason for not using ^/, though I fail to see what it could be right now.&#13;
&#13;
Work around is to specify view name as well, like:&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
RewriteRule ezcore/call/ /index_ajax.php [L]&#13;
RewriteRule ezcore/run/ /index_ajax.php [L]&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (André R)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezcore/forum/general/bug_wrong_rewriterule_in_ezcore_doc_ajax_txt/re_bug_wrong_rewriterule_in_ezcore_doc_ajax_txt</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2008 08:16:59 +0000</pubDate>
